WebElement inputField =
driver.findElement(By.id("insideText"));

String actual =
inputField.getAttribute("value");

Assert.assertEquals(actual,
                    "QA PlayGround");
If you specifically want to use your CSS selector approach, then:
String actualText =
driver.findElement(
    By.cssSelector("input[value='QA PlayGround']")
).getAttribute("value");

Assert.assertEquals(actualText,
                    "QA PlayGround");

--
Method	Reads
getText()	visible inner text
getAttribute()	HTML attribute value // <input value="QA PlayGround"></input>
